# Jump Hippo — shared local dev environment
#
# Copy this file to `dev.env` (git-ignored) and edit. The Makefile -includes it
# and exports the values, so `make debug` and `make launch` see the SAME
# settings.
#
#   cp dev.env.example dev.env
#
# Precedence: `make VAR=value` (one-off) > dev.env > your shell environment >
# the Makefile defaults. Lines are plain KEY=value (no `export`, no quotes).

# ── Dev toggles ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Reserved for future dev-only settings (e.g. a default bind host or linger for
# throwaway tunnels). None are read yet; this file exists so the shared dev-env
# pattern is in place from the start.
